news.title: Proposed amendments to Delhi Development Act gets mixed response
news.para: While developers and housing societies have supported the move for mandatory land pooling where a threshold of land has been pooled, others have flagged that such a move will result in more litigation and conflicts between farmers and landowners who are not willing to participate in the scheme.

news.title: Institutional investments in Indian real estate touch $3.6 billion in Jan-Sep: Colliers
news.para: As per the data, Delhi-NCR attracted institutional investments worth USD 754 million during the first nine months of this year, compared to USD 301 million in the year-ago period.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: New preferred spot? Registries up in non-NCR districts
news.para: Of a total of 8,116 units, 6,931 comes under residential head spread across 32 projects and 1,185 commercial units across four commercial projects.

news.title: Bengaluru: BDA commissioner, officials skip Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout meeting
news.para: ​​ Demanding the BDA authorities to complete land acquisition for the layout, Santosh Patil, who bought a site at the layout in 2016, said, “I want to commence construction of my house. I have been residing in a rented house.’’

news.title: Maharashtra CM asks realty developers to build iconic structures in Mumbai
news.para: “When we visit South Mumbai, we see iconic structures developed by the British. We are expecting each one of you to develop iconic structures in the city and create landmarks. You can tell us if any support is needed from the government’s side for this,” said Chief Minister Eknath Shinde.

news.title: SIT probing RERA scam to oppose pre-arrest bail of developers in Kalyan-Dombivli
news.para: The Special Investigation Team (SIT) probing the RERA scam by 66 developers in Kalyan-Dombivli has decided to oppose the pre-arrest bail application filed by three developers at Kalyan sessions court.

news.title: Delhi: Fire NOC no longer required for sanctioning building plans in special category
news.para: For the benefit of citizens, MCD has relaxed the condition of fire NOC for sanctioning building plans for residential properties in the special category, it said.

news.title: Chinese localities buy homes to work down high housing inventory
news.para: Homebuyers have moved cautiously even though more than 200 cities have taken steps to boost demand, offering subsidies, group-buying discounts, smaller down payments and cuts in mortgage interest rates.

news.title: KMRL plans to open Kochi metro phase II corridor in two years
news.para: KMRL authorities sought the support of public and people’s representatives to complete the project in a time-bound manner.

news.title: China's bursting housing bubble will rock the economy for years
news.para: While many economists say China’s crippling housing downturn won’t get much worse and that the stimulus will kick in this year or next, the reality on the ground for sellers like Echo is much bleaker.

news.title: PHED water for high-rises & residential complexes soon in Rajasthan
news.para: PHED minister Mahesh Joshi has announced that the policy to transfer pipeline water to high-rises and residential complexes in the city will be implemented by Diwali.

news.title: Now, website for enrolling partitions in land records in Punjab
news.para: ​Mann said citizens can apply on this website with details, including their name, father/husband name, village name, sub-tehsil/tehsil, district, khata and khewat number with simple application.

news.title: RDPR asked to share two gram panchayats' e-property data with Bengaluru civic body
news.para: This comes in the backdrop of several areas of Kaggalipura and Somashettyhalli gram panchayats being brought under BBMP’s ambit. The Palike has implemented e-property software for ease of services.

news.title: Not outskirts, most illegal constructions are in Bhopal
news.para: This year, three in ten complaints related to illegal construction have remained unresolved in the state capital. For every legal colony, there is almost one illegal colony in the state capital.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body to develop mini-township on 12 acres
news.para: The Ghaziabad Development Authority (GDA) is planning to revive the Indirapuram extension scheme, which was put on the back burner due to farmers’ protests over enhanced land compensation.
